main event: A small white star-like object was sighted in Mosinee, Wisconsin on April 22, 1964.
interesting points: The object was described as a rapidly moving star in straight flight from north to south.
The object disappeared in the distance after being observed for about 5 minutes.
The sighting was reported 5 days after it occurred.
The object was evaluated as likely being a satellite or 'shooting star' by the reporting official.
The observers were 4 students aged 14-20 years old, and their reliability was assessed as 'fair'.
